@startuml figure-3-7-activity-streak-checkin
title Figure 3.7 — Activity Diagram: Daily Healthy Smile Streak check-in\n(F15 + F16 — Asia/Amman date-key, streak math, badge award)

skinparam dpi 150
skinparam defaultFontName Cambria
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #E7EEF2
  BorderColor #1F2937
  FontColor #0F172A
  ArrowColor #334155
  ArrowFontSize 11
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FEF3C7
  DiamondBorderColor #92400E
  DiamondFontColor #0F172A
  StartColor #1F2937
  EndColor #1F2937
  BarColor #1F2937
}
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEF9C3
skinparam noteBorderColor #A16207
skinparam partition {
  BorderColor #94A3B8
  FontColor #0F172A
  FontStyle bold
}

|#FEF3C7| Patient |
start
:Open the Healthy Smile Streak page;

|#DBEAFE| Browser (Next.js 16) |
:GET /smile-streak/me;
:Render current streak,\nlongest streak, badges,\nand 3 ritual checkboxes\n(brush · floss · mouthwash);

|#FEF3C7| Patient |
:Tap the three\nritual checkboxes;

if (all three rituals checked?) then (no)
  :Submit button stays disabled;
  stop
else (yes)
endif

:Tap "Mark today done";

|#DBEAFE| Browser (Next.js 16) |
:POST /smile-streak/checkin\nheader: Authorization: Bearer <JWT>;

|#D1FAE5| NestJS — SmileStreakController + Service |
:Verify JWT via JwtAuthGuard\n(NFR-5);
:Compute today's Amman date key\n(YYYY-MM-DD in Asia/Amman,\nNFR-14, NFR-15);

if (SmileCheckin exists for (patient, todayKey)?) then (yes — already done today)
  :Return 409 Conflict\n{ alreadyCheckedInToday: true };

  |#DBEAFE| Browser (Next.js 16) |
  :Show "See you tomorrow"\ncelebration card;

  |#FEF3C7| Patient |
  stop
else (no)
endif

|#D1FAE5| NestJS — SmileStreakController + Service |
:Compute yesterday's Amman\ndate key (today − 1 day);

if (SmileCheckin exists for\n(patient, yesterdayKey)?) then (yes — streak continues)
  :newStreak = currentStreak + 1;
else (no — streak resets)
  :newStreak = 1;
endif

|#EDE9FE| Prisma 5.22 + PostgreSQL 16 |
:$transaction begin;
:INSERT INTO SmileCheckin\n(patientId, dateKey,\nstreakAt = newStreak);

if (newStreak > storedBest?) then (yes)
  :UPDATE bestStreak\non patient profile;
endif

if (newStreak ∈ {3, 7, 30, 100}?) then (yes — milestone)
  :INSERT INTO Notification\n(badge type, body);

  |#D1FAE5| NestJS — SmileStreakController + Service |
  :Award badge\n(F15 / FR-30);
else (no)
endif

|#EDE9FE| Prisma 5.22 + PostgreSQL 16 |
:tx commit;

|#D1FAE5| NestJS — SmileStreakController + Service |
:Return 201 Created\n{ newStreak, longestStreak,\nawardedBadge?, rank };

|#DBEAFE| Browser (Next.js 16) |
:Animate counter\nincrement;

if (badge awarded?) then (yes)
  :Trigger badge\nceremony animation;
else (no)
endif

:Refresh leaderboard\nranking widget\n(F16 / FR-31);

|#FEF3C7| Patient |
:See updated streak + badges;
stop

note right
  Date-key arithmetic uses Asia/Amman timezone for daily uniqueness
  regardless of server timezone (NFR-14, NFR-15). A patient who checks in
  at 11:45pm and again at 12:15am genuinely counts as two consecutive
  days, not one. The @@unique([patientId, dateKey]) constraint on
  SmileCheckin enforces one row per day at the storage layer.
end note

note left
  All inserts + updates run inside ONE Prisma $transaction (NFR-29):
  the SmileCheckin row, the bestStreak bump, and the badge Notification
  all commit together. If the badge insert fails the streak insert is
  rolled back too — the patient never sees a streak without its badge.
end note

@enduml
